\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs20 ANESTHESIA: General endotracheal tube.
\par PROCEDURE: After informed consent was obtained, the patient was brought to the operative suite and placed supine on the operating room table. General endotracheal anesthesia was induced without incident. The patient was prepped and draped in the usual sterile manner. Care was taken to ensure that the arm was placed in a relaxed manner away from the body to facilitate exposure and to avoid nerve injury.
\par incision overlying previous skin scar  was made to remove of silicone bag . The skin incision was carried down to the subcutaneous fat but no further. Using traction and counter-traction, silicone bag was removed without rupture.  Bovie electrocautery was used for the majority of the dissection and hemostasis tying only the large vessels with 2-0 Vicryl. fibrotic capsule was dissected from the pectoralis muscle beginning medially and progressing laterally removing the pectoralis fascia entirely. One H-VAC 200cc drains were inserted through separate stab incisions below the initial incision and cut to fit.  These were secured to the skin using 2-0 silk, which was Roman-sandaled around the drain.The skin incision was approximated with skin staples. A dressing was applied. The drains were placed on "grenade" suction. All surgical counts were reported as correct. Having tolerated the procedure well, the patient was subsequently extubated and taken to the recovery room in good and stable condition
